# 2. High Level Architecture

The game is divided into multiple systems. Each system has its own file so the project stays easy to maintain.

System flow:

Input System  
  ↓  
Player Logic  
  ↓  
Physics Engine  
  ↓  
Level Logic  
  ↓  
Camera System  
  ↓  
Rendering System

All systems are coordinated by the **main game loop in game.js**.

The goal of this architecture is to keep gameplay systems independent so new mechanics can be added without breaking existing code.

---

# 3. Game Loop Overview (game.js)

The entire game runs inside a loop that repeats every frame using:

requestAnimationFrame()

Simplified structure:

function gameLoop() {

  update();

  render();

  requestAnimationFrame(gameLoop);

}

The loop runs roughly **60 times per second** depending on the browser.

